: initialize bare/cache repo; fetch only `refs/meta/main`; no checkout, hooks, submodules, LFS, or arbitrary remotes; remote URL is constructed from GitHub’s canonical `full_name`.\n\n5. **Snapshot refresh semantics are half-deferred.**  \n   The doc says later requests re-fetch, but [Deferred](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md:662>) defers refresh/invalidation.\n\n   Add criteria: every stable PR-route request checks/fetches metadata; unchanged metadata OID may reuse snapshot; changed OID generates a new internal snapshot id.\n\n6. **Dedupe/ranking is not testable enough.**  \n   [Acceptance Criteria](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md:688>) says dedupe and rank, but [Deferred](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md:666>) defers exact dedupe behavior.\n\n   Add criteria: a session matching review and branch appears once, carries both match reasons, and ranks as a review match; tie-breakers are deterministic, probably newest matching turn then stable session id.\n\n7. **Bounds are vague.**  \n   “Bounded drill-down” and “too much data” appear, but there are no limits to test.\n\n   Add criteria: implementation defines constants for max sessions, turns per session, records per turn, and bytes per record/tool output; truncated responses expose `truncated: true` or equivalent UI state.\n\n8. **`but-agentlog` projection contract needs a minimum test shape.**  \n   The doc defers exact payload, but Forge cannot be tested without minimum fields.\n\n   Add criteria: projection includes stable session id, stable turn id, timestamps, match reasons, strength, compact display records, expandable record handles, and redaction-safe text only.\n\n9. **Redaction guarantees need fixture tests.**  \n   [Privacy And Publication](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md:552>) makes `but-agentlog` load-bearing. Good, but dangerous without tests.\n\n   Add criteria: fixtures containing local paths, provider session ids, hidden/system/developer prompts, and oversized tool output must not render through the public projection.\n\n10. **Noindex is missing from acceptance.**  \n   [line 579](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md:579>) says public but not promoted.\n\n   Add criteria: rendered pages include `noindex`, via header or meta tag, with a test.\n\n**Test Plan I’d Want**\n\n- Unit tests: route parsing, canonicalization, target construction, ranking/dedupe.\n- GitHub API mock tests: public PR, private/not found, fork PR, rate limit, outage.\n- Git fetch tests: exact `refs/meta/main` fetch, missing ref, fetch failure, OID pinning.\n- Projection tests: public/read output shape, redaction fixtures, truncation flags.\n- Page tests: PR identity, snapshot OID, status state, match badges, weak branch separation, bounded evidence drawer.\n- Concurrency test: two first requests for the same repo share/lock initialization.\n\nNo must-ask questions from me before building. These are doc hardening items, not product blockers.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:06:24.619Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}